R Lab 4 - Joins

Author

Byeong-Hak Choe

Loading R packages

library(tidyverse)
library(nycflights13)
library(skimr)

Question 1

Consider the following example DataFrames.

student_data1 <- data.frame(
  student_id = c('S1', 'S2', 'S3', 'S4', 'S5'),
  name = c('Danniella Fenton', 'Ryder Storey', 'Bryce Jensen', 'Ed Bernal', 'Kwame Morin'),
  marks = c(200, 210, 190, 222, 199)
)

student_data2 <- data.frame(
  student_id = c('S4', 'S5', 'S6', 'S7', 'S8'),
  name = c('Scarlette Fisher', 'Carla Williamson', 'Dante Morse', 'Kaiser William', 'Madeeha Preston'),
  marks = c(201, 200, 198, 219, 201)
)


Q1a

Write a R code to join the two given data.frames along rows and assign all data.


Q1b

Write a R code to join the two given data.frames along columns and assign all data.




Question 2

Consider the three data.frames flights, airports, and airlines from the nycflights13 package.

  • flights data.frame
colnames(flights)  # returns column names in the flights data.frame
 [1] "year"           "month"          "day"            "dep_time"      
 [5] "sched_dep_time" "dep_delay"      "arr_time"       "sched_arr_time"
 [9] "arr_delay"      "carrier"        "flight"         "tailnum"       
[13] "origin"         "dest"           "air_time"       "distance"      
[17] "hour"           "minute"         "time_hour"
  • airports data.frame
colnames(airports)  
[1] "faa"   "name"  "lat"   "lon"   "alt"   "tz"    "dst"   "tzone"
  • airlines data.frame
colnames(airlines)
[1] "carrier" "name"


Q2a

Join flights with airports, so that we can see information about each flights destination airport in the flights data.frame.


Q2b

Find the full name of the airline that has the longest positive dep_delay on average.


Q2c

Find the full name of the airline that has the largest proportion of flights with longer than 30-minute dep_delay.
